The paper deals with the management of uncertainty in expert systems, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of different calculi of uncertainty and the selection of the most appropriate one for a given situation involves machine learning and decision-making, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of families of triangular norms and conorms, which are mathematical concepts related to fuzzy logic and set theory, respectively, suggesting that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
